sentences: Charles Elzer Loudermilk (July 7, 1927 – January 26, 2011), known professionally as Charlie Louvin, was an American country music singer and songwriter.
He is best known as one of the Louvin Brothers, and was a member of the Grand Ole Opry since 1955.
He started singing when he was eight years old.
